Employment: As an Accounts Payable Associate, my role is essential in ensuring the smooth and efficient financial operations of | Accenture Solutions Pvt Ltd | 2021-Present | a organization. My primary responsibility is to manage and process all incoming invoices and payments owed to vendors, suppliers, and service providers also verifying the accuracy and completeness of invoices, matching them with purchase orders or contracts, and reconciling any discrepancies that may arise. As an integral part of the finance team, I am attention to detail at organizational skills, and a good understanding of accounting principles which is crucial in performing my duties effectively & efficiently in managing all the accounts payable process, and to contribute to the company''s financial stability and maintain positive relationships with vendors, ultimately helping the organization achieve its financial goals and maintain a solid reputation in the business community. www.resumekraft.com My main roles and responsibilities:  Timely and accurate processing of PO and NON-PO invoices: Ensure that invoices are entered into the SAP system promptly and with the correct information. Verify the accuracy of the invoices against purchase orders or service agreements before processing.  Performing month-end Accrual activities: At the end of each month, calculate and record accruals for any expenses or services that have been received but not yet invoiced. This helps in maintaining accurate financial records.  Timely resolution of client queries: Being responsive to client inquiries related to invoices and payments. Promptly investigate and resolve any discrepancies or issues to ensure smooth business relations.  Processing of Rush payments: Handle urgent or rush payments with efficiency, ensuring that the required approvals and documentation are in place while meeting the payment deadlines.  Maintaining of detailed and organized records of all invoices, payments, and related documentation for reference and audit purposes.  Implementing controls and checks to prevent duplicate payments, such as cross-referencing invoices and payment records before processing.  SLA reporting: Monitor and report on key performance indicators (KPIs) related to invoice processing, like turnaround time, accuracy, and query resolution, to ensure compliance with service level agreements.  Delegating work among the team: If you are in a supervisory role, assign tasks and responsibilities to team members based on their skills and expertise, ensuring an efficient workflow.  Cross-trained in different countries: If you work in a multinational environment, consider getting cross-trained on invoice processing practices in different countries to handle international transactions effectively.  Updating process manuals: Regularly review and update process manuals to reflect any changes in invoice processing procedures and ensure everyone follows standardized practices.  High-value invoice audit: Pay special attention to high-value invoices to perform a thorough audit, ensuring accuracy and compliance with financial controls.  By fulfilling these responsibilities, you can contribute significantly to the efficient and effective invoice processing in SAP and support the financial operations of your organization. Applications SAP-FS2, MS – Office, Word, PowerPoint, Tally ERP 9

